header.title: GRAPPLE
header.description: This tutorial explains GRAPPLE, from setup to end-user learner, teacher and administrator. The tutorial itself refers to separate tutorials for different parts of GRAPPLE: the setup of a Learning Management System (LMS), the GRAPPLE event bus (GEB), the GRAPPLE user modeling framework (GUMF), the GRAPPLE authoring tool (GAT) and the GRAPPLE adaptive learning environment (GALE). GRAPPLE contains additional elements, for visualization, virtual reality and simulation, not covered by this tutorial (at this time).

header.title: G-Public-Knowledge
header.description: Publishes the (updates to the) knowledge attribute to GUMF.

header.title: G-Knowledge-Propagation-Parent
header.description: This propagates knowledge updates to the parent concept. (This PRT should be used automatically in any Course over a Domain with the "parent" relatinoship, but it doesn't so this needs to be done manually.)

crt.comment: This PRT arranges for knowledge changes to be propagated upwards in the concept hierarchy. Knowledge is propagated to the parent, and this update triggers the PRT update for that parent. The basic idea is for this PRT to be automatically applied to the domain relation "parent" but alas this does not work yet, so all concepts need to be placed in the socket manually. This is a "convenience" PRT: knowledge can also be propagated using the "G-Knowledge-Propagation" PRT but this is a binary PRT that requires the creation of many instance whereas the G-knowledge-Propagation-Parent PRT does the propagation automatically for all parent relationships by inserting concepts into the socket of a single instance.

header.title: G-Public-Visited
